body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/452\n\n## Problem\n`pm plan materialize --materialize-type <T>` dead-ends when type T has a --required-on-create custom field: materialize has no way to pass custom-field values, fails missing_required_option per step. Any governed schema (required acceptance_owner etc.) breaks the plan -> materialize -> task loop; workaround defeats typed materialization.\n\n## Proposed fix\nLet materialize supply custom-field values (--field key=value per step or plan-level defaults), and/or let required-on-create policies exempt system-driven creates with an explicit policy knob. Prefer explicit --field passthrough (keeps governance intact).\n\n## Definition of done\nMaterialize succeeds for types with required-on-create custom fields via documented passthrough; spec covers required-field + materialize interplay; docs plan section updated."
